<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.13/29.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Scholle</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your October 3. I called upon the President this afternoon to discuss the
                            Amnesty Bill. He said he was pleased to receive my note giving the view
                            of the Government of the United States as it helped him to prove to the
                            leaders of the House and Senate that the bill was bad legislation. He
                            assured me that he would veto it on the ground of unconstitutionality
                            and because of the bad effect upon Cuba’s reputation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Scholle</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>